<br>
Being the member of any  recreational activity &quot;club&quot; it is certainly not nice to be taken of the team........<br>
<br>
True EQ is a game.<br>
<br>
Untrue you can do as you please since it don't matter, it is just a game. <br>
What you do and how other players acts towards you will affect you. For some it might affect them too much....<br>
<br>
But most people playing on a regular basis are affected at least in game by how they are treated.<br>
Just look how mad ks'ing or ninjalooting will get people.<br>
<br>
So what is a guild? A comforting writing some obscure out of the way spot on the screen? &quot;Oh I am in a guild I am not alone, how nice&quot;?<br>
<br>
Some people pour a ton of effort into building a community within EQ working towards the same aims. The satisfaction when the reach a step on the way are immense for them. <br>
<br>
This can be a small guild trying to get an epic piece for their only high level mage.....Or a raiding guild trying to gain access to a new plane.......<br>
<br>
But what if a player in the small guild loot the piece the guild got for their mage? He have a newly rolled mage and want to mq that part? What sanction do the guild have?<br>
<br>
Well they can call on a GM and ask him to get the piece back... <br>
<br>
Trust have been broken and most likely they will turn to the only sanction they them selves hold. They will remove that player from the guild.<br>
<br>
So why is it so bad to be removed? Because it is a punishment. Be it just or not... When you are guild removed it is a punishment. If you look through old posts you will find several players dissatisfied that they were removed because they no longer met the guilds requirements.<br>
<br>
They knew they did not meet those requirements... But their friends, their goals and their ingame identity was tied in with that guild. They thought somehow that they could pickup and get a second chance. Some thought it was their right to do so. <br>
<br>
This is just a game, lighten up....<br>
<br>
The people are real, never forget it. <br>
Your ingame desires are real, and you will work on those.<br>
The satisfaction that comes with achieving a goal is real.<br>
The hurt by being mistreated are real, EQ is a game, but you are real... you can't pretend you are pixels. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#0E0E0E><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub169.ezboard.com/bmtboards.showUserPublicProfile?gid=neffylim>Neffylim</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Riding the Planes</span><br>  Posts: 654<br> <font color=#AAAAAA>(9/3/03 2:11 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub169.ezboard.com/fmtboardsfrm40.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=81.topic&index=26>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: .......</span><hr size=1> <!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr>well, except those of you who do know who every single person is in the game.<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
