<br>
The rule states<br>
<br>
2) No posts may be made anonymously. Your characters name in game must be made known if you are to put another character's name on the Most-Hated list.<br>
<br>
Fortunately for Itcey his main character, the one he's posting about is Itcey.  Hence, he's not Anonymous...<br>
<br>
If the rule stated<br>
<br>
2) No posts may be made anonymously. Your characters name in game must be made known if you are to put another character's name on the Most-Hated list.  This should be done by placing a sig of your main character at the bottom of your post.<br>
<br>
I'd agree with you Calalily.  As it is, your just being stubborn.  So fix the rule or fix the post.  Ask Kelmore or Fimble to &quot;fix&quot; the rules post to reflect the actual rules then.<br>
<br>
Further, even if I put a &quot;label&quot; at the bottom of my post, does that make it a known character or does it just get by the &quot;moron&quot; filter then.  IMO It gets by the newly established &quot;moron&quot; filter.<br>
<br>
Why?<br>
<br>
Anyone can create an EZ Board account, any day of the week with someone elses name and sign it someone else and you, Cala, think its authentic.  <br>
<br>
When here is someone who quite obviously created an EZ Board account with their characters name, and provided a link to the guild website they are still hosting.  Then you hoist yourself up by your &quot;power&quot; to enforce this rule.  Then when people post he is a main character and isn't posting anonymously, you don't have the internal fortitude, to say, <br>
<br>
&quot;Yes I made a mistake, let me move it back&quot;<br>
<br>
Or<br>
<br>
&quot;Your right, it doesn't say a sig is required in the rules, I 'll have that fixed.&quot;<br>
<br>
Instead you fight tooth and nail to keep your thoughtless &quot;enforcement&quot; going.<br>
<br>
So will Kelmore or Fimble to fix the rule to say you need a sig since its the only thing they can do that won't usurp your power and hurt your feelings.<br>
