<br>
When you work with a point system for loot that power is augmented because members are unwilling to object or rebel against the Guildleader because they have invested time into the guild and they have a number points invested into the loot system to keep them inline.<br>
<br>
What Sony needs to do is implement a function where a Guildleader can be removed by the majority of the officers and that it will take a majority of the officers (as the GL will considered an officer) to remove other officers.<br>
<br>
This way.  The GL does not have absolute power over the functions of a guild.  I suspect that if this ever happens Many GL will be tossed on their asses and have to answer for the decisions they make.  Giving the officers of a guild the power to remove or elect a GL will make guilds act more like a democracy then a monarchy.<br>
<br>
I am not saying the system I'm suggesting above is what should be implemented..I'm just saying some sort of check and balance needs to be created to insure that Guilds that you invest your time in is more of a community then a kingdom.<br>
<br>
I am sure if this ever happened in EQ many Guildleaders would find themselves deguilded before they could finish downloading the patch.<br>
